CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1776769395
OL,3,CWarm days, cold nights: What is behind
OL,4,Cthis week's big temperature gap?
OL,6,FInterestingly, although the sun tends
OL,7,Fto actually be at the same strength in
OL,8,FSeptember as in April, the diurnal
OL,9,Frange tends to be a lot smaller in
OL,10,Fautumn because the ground is still
OL,11,Fretaining heat from the warm summer
OL,12,Fmonths, and this tends to mitigate the
OL,13,Fheat loss overnight (just like a
OL,14,Fnighttime storage heater holds
OL,15,Ftemperatures up overnight in your
OL,16,Fhome).
OL,18,FHow is the diurnal range useful for
OL,19,Fforecasting?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
