PN,30806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1776769395
OL,3,CWarm days, cold nights: What is behind
OL,4,Cthis week's big temperature gap?
OL,6,FYou only have to look at shivering
OL,7,Fevening revellers to see how easy it
OL,8,Fis to be caught out at this time of
OL,9,Fyear - and the cold can have some
OL,10,Fserious implications when temperatures
OL,11,Fdrop around or below freezing.
OL,13,FCrops - particularly many vegetable
OL,14,Fand fruit crops - can be damaged by
OL,15,Fprolonged frosts, and lambs born in
OL,16,Fspring can quickly get into difficulty
OL,17,Fin sudden cold weather. Driving
OL,18,Fconditions can be tricky if roads ice
OL,19,Fover, so anticipating cold nights
OL,20,Ftriggers gritting lorries to go out
OL,21,Feven quite late into the spring.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1776769395
OL,3,CWarm days, cold nights: What is behind
OL,4,Cthis week's big temperature gap?
OL,6,FIn short, the diurnal range acts like
OL,7,Fa quick diagnostic tool - it helps
OL,8,Fforecasters understand temperature
OL,9,Fbehaviour, atmospheric conditions, and
OL,10,Fpotential weather hazards.
OL,12,FWhy is it so big this week?
OL,14,FA few factors are at play here: the
OL,15,Fmonth of April typically gives us the
OL,16,Fbiggest diurnal range of the year; the
OL,17,Fsun is just about strong enough to
OL,18,Fallow temperatures to rocket up during
OL,19,Fthe day but still fall back rapidly at
OL,20,Fnight.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1776769395
OL,3,CWarm days, cold nights: What is behind
OL,4,Cthis week's big temperature gap?
OL,6,FThis week will bring plenty of
OL,7,Fsunshine to boost temperatures into
OL,8,Fthe high teens over the next few days,
OL,9,Fbut then clear overnight skies will
OL,10,Fsee them rapidly falling away again.
OL,12,FSo bear that in mind if you're out in
OL,13,Fthe evening and don't be fooled by a
OL,14,Fwarm afternoon, you'll be shivering by
OL,15,Fearly evening if you don't take an
OL,16,Fextra layer - and it's all down to the
OL,17,Flarge April diurnal range!
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
